By Esther Egbe

Former Cameroon captain Samuel Eto’o wants to leave Turkish Super League outfit Antalyaspor for a club which will recognize his true worth.

National Daily gathered that the 36-year-old forward, who joined Antalyaspor in 2015, has had a good spell with the club impressively scoring 38 goals in 62 league matches.

However, his agent Wilfried de Happi has revealed that the four-time African Player of the Year is eager to leave the Scorpions


			
